205 template<typename DataType_, int k_ = 1>
206 class SineTensorStatic
207 {
208 static_assert(k_ > 0, "parameter k_ must be a positive integer");
209
210 public:
212 static DataType_ kpi()
213 {
214 return DataType_(k_) * Math::pi<DataType_>();
215 }
216
218 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
219 {
220 return Math::sin(kpi() * x);
221 }
222
224 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
225 {
226 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
227 }
228
230 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
231 {
232 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
233 }
234
236 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
237 {
238 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x);
239 }
240
242 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
243 {
244 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
245 }
246
248 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
249 {
250 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
251 }
252
254 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
255 {
256 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
257 }
258
260 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
261 {
262 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
263 }
264
266 static DataType_ der_z(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
267 {
268 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
269 }
270
272 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
273 {
274 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x);
275 }
276
278 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
279 {
280 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
281 }
282
284 static DataType_ der_yy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
285 {
286 return der_xx(x, y);
287 }
288
290 static DataType_ der_xy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
291 {
292 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
293 }
294
296 static DataType_ der_yx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
297 {
298 return der_xy(x, y);
299 }
300
302 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
303 {
304 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
305 }
306
308 static DataType_ der_yy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
309 {
310 return der_xx(x, y, z);
311 }
312
314 static DataType_ der_zz(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
315 {
316 return der_xx(x, y, z);
317 }
318
320 static DataType_ der_xy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
321 {
322 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
323 }
324
326 static DataType_ der_yx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
327 {
328 return der_xy(x, y, z);
329 }
330
332 static DataType_ der_xz(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
333 {
334 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
335 }

579 template<typename DataType_>
580 class ExpBubbleScalarStatic
581 {
582 public:
584 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
585 {
586 return (Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1))) / (DataType_(1) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1)));
587 }
588
590 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
591 {
592 return (DataType_(8)*x - DataType_(4))*Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
593 }
594
596 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
597 {
598 return (DataType_(64)*x*(DataType_(1)-x)-DataType_(8)) * Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
599 }
600 }; // class ExpBubbleScalarStatic<...>

858 template<typename AnalyticFunctionType1, typename AnalyticFunctionType2>
859 class MinOfTwoFunctions :
860 public Analytic::Function
861 {
862 public:
864 static_assert(AnalyticFunctionType1::domain_dim == AnalyticFunctionType2::domain_dim, "domain dimension mismatch");
865
867 static_assert(std::is_same<typename AnalyticFunctionType1::ImageType, Analytic::Image::Scalar>::value, "invalid image type");
868 static_assert(std::is_same<typename AnalyticFunctionType2::ImageType, Analytic::Image::Scalar>::value, "invalid image type");
869
871 static constexpr int domain_dim = AnalyticFunctionType1::domain_dim;
873 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
874
876 static constexpr bool can_value = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_value && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_value);
878 static constexpr bool can_grad = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_grad && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_grad);
880 static constexpr bool can_hess = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_hess && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_hess);
881
882 public:
884 template<typename EvalTraits_>
885 class Evaluator :
886 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
887 {
888 public:
890 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
892 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
894 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
896 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
898 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
899
900 private:
902 typename AnalyticFunctionType1::template Evaluator<EvalTraits_> _f1_eval;
904 typename AnalyticFunctionType2::template Evaluator<EvalTraits_> _f2_eval;
905
906 const DataType _eps;
907
908 public:
910 explicit Evaluator(const MinOfTwoFunctions& function) :
911 _f1_eval(function._f1),
912 _f2_eval(function._f2),
913 _eps(Math::eps<DataType>())
914 {
915 }
916
917 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
918 {
919 return Math::min(_f1_eval.value(point), _f2_eval.value(point));
920 }
921
922 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
923 {
924 ValueType val1 = _f1_eval.value(point);
925 ValueType val2 = _f2_eval.value(point);
926
927 if(Math::abs(val1-val2) < _eps)
928 return GradientType::null();
929 else if(val1 < val2)
930 return _f1_eval.gradient(point);
931 else
932 return _f2_eval.gradient(point);
933 }
934
935 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
936 {
937 ValueType val1 = _f1_eval.value(point);
938 ValueType val2 = _f2_eval.value(point);
939
940 if(Math::abs(val1-val2) < _eps)
941 return HessianType::null();
942 else if(val1 < val2)
943 return _f1_eval.hessian(point);
944 else
945 return _f2_eval.hessian(point);
946 }
947 }; // class MinOfTwoFunctions::Evaluator<...>
948
949 private:
951 const AnalyticFunctionType1& _f1;
953 const AnalyticFunctionType2& _f2;
954
955 public:
957 explicit MinOfTwoFunctions(const AnalyticFunctionType1& f1_, const AnalyticFunctionType2& f2_) :
958 _f1(f1_),
959 _f2(f2_)
960 {
961 }
962 }; // class MinOfTwoFunctions

984 template<typename DataType_>

1053 template<typename DataType_>
1054 class HeavisideRegStatic
1055 {
1056 public:
1057
1059 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
1060 {
1061 return ( x < DataType_(0) ) ? DataType_(0) : DataType_(2)*(Math::cosh(x) - DataType_(1));
1062 }
1063
1065 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
1066 {
1067 return eval(x)*eval(y);
1068 }
1069
1071 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
1072 {
1073 return eval(x)*eval(y)*eval(z);
1074 }
1075

1234 class PolynomialFunction1D :
1235 public Analytic::Function
1236 {
1237 public:

1250 template<typename EvalTraits_>
1251 class Evaluator :
1252 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
1253 {
1254 public:
1255 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
1256 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
1257 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
1258 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
1259 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
1260
1261 private:
1263 std::vector<DataType> _coeff;
1264
1265 public:
1267 explicit Evaluator(const PolynomialFunction1D& function)
1268 {
1269 for(auto it = function._coeff.begin(); it != function._coeff.end(); ++it)
1270 _coeff.push_back(DataType(*it));
1271 }
1272
1273 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1274 {
1275 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1276 DataType x = point[0];
1277 DataType y = DataType(0);
1278 for(std::size_t k(_coeff.size()); k > std::size_t(0); )
1279 y = x * y + _coeff[--k];
1280
1281 return y;
1282 }
1283
1284 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1285 {
1286 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1287 if(k <= std::size_t(0))
1288 return GradientType::null();
1289
1290 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1291 DataType x = point[0];
1292 DataType y = DataType(0);
1293 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(0); )
1294 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k));
1295
1296 return GradientType(y);
1297 }
1298
1299 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1300 {
1301 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1302 if(k <= std::size_t(1))
1303 return HessianType::null();
1304
1305 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1306 DataType x = point[0];
1307 DataType y = DataType(0);
1308 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(1); )
1309 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k*(k-1)));
1310
1311 return HessianType(y);
1312 }
1313 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D::Evaluator
1314
1315 private:
1317 std::vector<DataType_> _coeff;
1318
1319 public:
1321 PolynomialFunction1D() :
1322 _coeff()
1323 {
1324 }
1325
1332 explicit PolynomialFunction1D(std::initializer_list<DataType_> coeff) :
1333 _coeff(coeff)
1334 {
1335 }
1336
1349 Index set_coeff(Index degree, DataType_ coeff)
1350 {
1351 // check degree
1352 if(Index(_coeff.size()) <= degree)
1353 _coeff.resize(std::size_t(degree+1), DataType_(0));
1354
1355 // set coefficient
1356 _coeff.at(std::size_t(degree)) = coeff;
1357
1358 // return degree+1
1359 return Index(_coeff.size());
1360 }
1361 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D

1714 DataType_ _vmax;
1715
1716 public:
1723 ParProfileBase() :
1724 _x0(0.0), _y0(0.0), _x1(0.0), _y1(1.0), _vmax(1.0)
1725 {
1726 }
1727
1740 explicit ParProfileBase(DataType_ x0, DataType_ y0, DataType_ x1, DataType_ y1, DataType_ vmax = DataType_(1.0)) :
1741 _x0(x0), _y0(y0), _x1(x1), _y1(y1), _vmax(vmax)
1742 {
1743 }
1744
1762 bool parse(const String& sbc)
1763 {
1764 auto li = sbc.find_first_of('(');
1765 auto ri = sbc.find_last_of(')');
1766 if((li == sbc.npos) || (ri == sbc.npos))
1767 return false;
1768
1769 std::deque<String> sv = sbc.substr(li+1, ri-li-1).split_by_string(",");
1770 if((sv.size() < std::size_t(2)) || (sv.size() > std::size_t(3)))
1771 return false;
1772
1773 std::deque<String> sv0 = sv[0].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
1774 std::deque<String> sv1 = sv[1].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
1775 if(sv0.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
1776 if(sv1.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
1777
1778 if(!sv0[0].parse(_x0)) return false;
1779 if(!sv0[1].parse(_y0)) return false;
1780 if(!sv1[0].parse(_x1)) return false;
1781 if(!sv1[1].parse(_y1)) return false;
1782
1783 if((sv.size() == std::size_t(3)) && !sv.back().parse(_vmax))
1784 return false;
1785
1786 return true;
1787 }
1788 }; // class ParProfileBase

1799 class ParProfileScalar :
1800 public ParProfileBase<DataType_>
1801 {
1802 public:
1803 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;
1804 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
1805 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
1806 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
1807 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
1808
1809 using ParProfileBase<DataType_>::ParProfileBase;
1810
1811 template<typename Traits_>
1812 class Evaluator :
1813 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
1814 {
1815 protected:
1816 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
1817 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
1818 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
1819 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
1820 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
1821
1822 PointType _vo, _ve;
1823 DataType _den, _vmax;
1824
1825 public:
1826 explicit Evaluator(const ParProfileScalar& function)
1827 {
1828 _vo[0] = DataType(function._x0);
1829 _vo[1] = DataType(function._y0);
1830 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
1831 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);
1832 _den = DataType(1) / Tiny::dot(_ve, _ve);
1833 _vmax = DataType(function._vmax);
1834 }
1835
1836 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
1837 {
1838 // project point onto line segment
1839 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
1840 // compute function value
1841 return _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
1842 }
1843
1844 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
1845 {
1846 // project point onto line segment
1847 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1848
1849 // Note: the gradient has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1850 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1851 return GradientType::null();
1852
1853 return (_vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x)) * _ve;
1854 }
1855
1856 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
1857 {
1858 // project point onto line segment
1859 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1860
1861 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1862 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1863 return HessianType::null();
1864
1865 HessianType hess;
1866 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
1867 hess[0][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1868 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1869 hess[1][1] = v * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1870 return hess;
1871 }
1872 };
1873 }; // class ParProfileScalar

1896 template<typename Traits_>
1897 class Evaluator :
1898 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
1899 {
1900 protected:
1901 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
1902 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
1903 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
1904 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
1905 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
1906
1907 PointType _vo, _ve, _vn;
1908 DataType _den, _vmax;
1909
1910 public:
1911 explicit Evaluator(const ParProfileVector& function)
1912 {
1913 _vo[0] = DataType(function._x0);
1914 _vo[1] = DataType(function._y0);
1915 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
1916 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);
1917 _vn[0] = _ve[1];
1918 _vn[1] = -_ve[0];
1919 _vn.normalize();
1920 _den = DataType(1) / Tiny::dot(_ve, _ve);
1921 _vmax = DataType(function._vmax);
1922 }
1923
1924 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
1925 {
1926 // project point onto line segment
1927 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
1928 // compute function value
1929 const DataType v = _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
1930 ValueType val;
1931 val[0] = _vn[0] * v;
1932 val[1] = _vn[1] * v;
1933 return val;
1934 }
1935
1936 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
1937 {
1938 // project point onto line segment
1939 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1940
1941 // Note: the gradient has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1942 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1943 return GradientType::null();
1944
1945 const DataType v = _vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x);
1946 GradientType grad;
1947 grad(0,0) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0];
1948 grad(0,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[1];
1949 grad(1,0) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0];
1950 grad(1,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[1];
1951 return grad;
1952 }
1953
1954 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
1955 {
1956 // project point onto line segment
1957 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1958
1959 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1960 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1961 return HessianType::null();
1962
1963 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
1964 HessianType hess;
1965 hess(0,0,0) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1966 hess(0,1,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1967 hess(0,1,0) = hess(0,0,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1968 hess(1,1,0) = hess(1,0,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1969 hess(1,0,0) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1970 hess(1,1,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1971 return hess;
1972 }
1973 };

2900 {
2901 const DataType x = point[0];
2902 const DataType y = point[1];
2903 const DataType z = point[2];
2904 const DataType re = DataType(1) / point.norm_euclid();
2905 const DataType cx = Math::cos(pi * re * x);
2906 const DataType cy = Math::cos(pi * re * y);
2907 const DataType cz = Math::cos(pi * re * z);

2909 const DataType sy = Math::sin(pi * re * y);
2910 const DataType sz = Math::sin(pi * re * z);
2911 GradientType grad;
2912 grad[0] = +pi * Math::cub(re) * (cx*sz*sy*y*y + cx*sz*sy*z*z - sx*x*y*cy*sz - sx*sy*x*z*cz);
2913 grad[1] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*y*cx*sy*sz - sz*sx*cy*x*x - sz*sx*cy*z*z + sx*sy*z*y*cz);
2914 grad[2] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*z*cx*sy*sz + sx*z*y*cy*sz - sx*cz*sy*x*x - sx*cz*sy*y*y);
2915 return grad;

3420 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
3421 {
3422 public:
3424 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
3426 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
3428 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
3430 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
3432 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
3433
3434 private:
3435 const PointType _origin;
3436 const PointType _axis;
3437 const DataType _v_max;
3438 const DataType _radius_s;
3439
3440 public:
3441 explicit Evaluator(const PoiseuillePipeFlow& function) :
3442 _origin(function.origin),
3443 _axis(PointType(function.axis).normalize()),
3444 _v_max(function.v_max),
3445 _radius_s(DataType(1) / Math::sqr(function.radius))
3446 {
3447 }
3448
3449 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
3450 {
3451 // compute ray to project point onto axis
3452 const PointType q = _origin + Tiny::dot(point - _origin, _axis) * _axis - point;
3453 // compute velocity based on distance to axis and in direction of axis
3454 return _v_max * (DataType(1) - q.norm_euclid_sqr()*_radius_s) * _axis;
3455 }
3456
3457 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
3458 {
3459 // compute ray to project point onto axis
3460 const PointType q = _origin + Tiny::dot(point - _origin, _axis) * _axis - point;
3461 // compute gradient
3462 GradientType grad = GradientType::null();
3463 //grad.add_outer_product(_axis, Tiny::dot(_axis, q)*_axis - q, -DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max);
3464 grad.set_outer_product(_axis, q);
3465 grad.add_outer_product(_axis, _axis, -Tiny::dot(_axis, q));
3466 return DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max * grad;
3467 }
3468
3469 HessianType hessian(const PointType&) const
3470 {
3471 // seriously, getting this mumbo jumbo below right was mostly a lucky guess...
3472 GradientType grad_q = GradientType::null();
3473 grad_q.set_outer_product(_axis, _axis);
3474 grad_q.add_scalar_main_diag(-DataType(1));
3475 GradientType at_x_a;
3476 at_x_a.set_outer_product(_axis, _axis);
3477 HessianType hess = HessianType::null();
3478 hess.add_vec_mat_outer_product(_axis, grad_q);
3479 hess.add_vec_mat_outer_product(_axis * grad_q, at_x_a, -DataType(1));
3480 return DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max * hess;
3481 }

3653 template<typename DT_>

3655 {
3656 public:

3660 typedef Analytic::Image::Vector<2> ImageType;
3662 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;

3673 template<typename EvalTraits_>
3674 class Evaluator :
3675 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
3676 {
3677 public:
3679 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
3681 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
3683 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
3685 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
3687 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
3688
3689 private:
3691 const DataType _pi2;
3692
3693 public:
3694 explicit Evaluator(const SineRingVortexVelo2D&) :
3695 _pi2(DataType(2) * Math::pi<DataType>())
3696 {
3697 }
3698
3699 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
3700 {
3701 ValueType val = ValueType::null();
3702 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3703 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3704 return val;
3705
3706 const DataType s2pdi = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) / d;
3707
3708 val[0] = point[1]*s2pdi;
3709 val[1] = -point[0]*s2pdi;
3710 return val;
3711 }
3712
3713 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
3714 {
3715 GradientType grad = GradientType::null();
3716 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3717 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3718 return grad;
3719
3720 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
3721 const DataType di2 = DataType(1) / (d*d);
3722 const DataType s2pdi = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) / d;
3723 const DataType c2pdi2 = Math::cos(_pi2 * d) * di2;
3724
3725 grad[0][0] = -y*x*s2pdi*di2 + _pi2*y*x*c2pdi2;
3726 grad[0][1] = -y*y*s2pdi*di2 + _pi2*y*y*c2pdi2 + s2pdi;
3727 grad[1][0] = x*x*s2pdi*di2 - _pi2*x*x*c2pdi2 - s2pdi;
3728 grad[1][1] = x*y*s2pdi*di2 - _pi2*y*x*c2pdi2;
3729 return grad;
3730 }
3731
3732 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
3733 {
3734 HessianType hess = HessianType::null();
3735 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3736 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3737 return hess;
3738
3739 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
3740 const DataType di2 = DataType(1) / (d*d);
3741 const DataType s2pdi3 = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) * di2 / d;
3742 const DataType c2pdi2 = Math::cos(_pi2 * d) * di2;
3743 const DataType t3 = DataType(3);
3744
3745 hess[0][0][0] = t3*y*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 - t3*_pi2*y*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 - y*s2pdi3 + _pi2*y*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*x*x*s2pdi3;
3746 hess[0][0][1] =
3747 hess[0][1][0] = t3*y*y*x*s2pdi3*di2 - x*s2pdi3 - t3*_pi2*y*y*x*c2pdi2*di2 + _pi2*x*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*y*x*s2pdi3;
3748 hess[0][1][1] = t3*y*y*y*s2pdi3*di2 - t3*y*s2pdi3 - t3*_pi2*y*y*y*c2pdi2*di2 + t3*_pi2*y*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*y*y*s2pdi3;
3749 hess[1][0][0] = -t3*x*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 + t3*x*s2pdi3 + t3*_pi2*x*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 - t3*_pi2*x*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*x*x*x*s2pdi3;
3750 hess[1][0][1] =
3751 hess[1][1][0] = -t3*y*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 + t3*_pi2*y*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 + y*s2pdi3 - _pi2*y*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*y*x*x*s2pdi3;
3752 hess[1][1][1] = -t3*y*y*x*s2pdi3*di2 + x*s2pdi3 + t3*_pi2*y*y*x*c2pdi2*di2 - _pi2*x*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*y*y*x*s2pdi3;
3753 return hess;
3754 }
3755 }; // class SineRingVortexVelo2D::Evaluator<...>

4015 hess.format();
4016 for(int i = 0; i < dim_; ++i)
4017 {

4019 {
4020 if(i == j)
4021 {
4022 hess[i][j] = DataType(0);
4023 for(int k = 0; k < dim_; ++k)
4024 hess[i][j] += (k == i ? DataType(-a_) : Math::sqr(point[k])) * s;
4025 }

4064 template<typename DT_>
4065 class CornerSingularity2D :
4066 public Analytic::Function
4067 {
4068 public:
4069 typedef DT_ DataType;
4070 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;
4071 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
4072 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
4073 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
4074 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
4075
4076 private:
4077 Tiny::Vector<DataType, 2> base_point;
4078 DataType alpha, k, offset;
4079
4080 public:
4081 CornerSingularity2D() = delete;
4082
4083 CornerSingularity2D(const Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2>& center, Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2> v_1, Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2> v_2, DT_ alpha_ = DT_(1.)) :
4084 base_point(center),
4085 alpha(alpha_)
4086 {
4087 ASSERTM((v_1.norm_euclid_sqr() > Math::eps<DataType>()) && (v_2.norm_euclid_sqr() > Math::eps<DataType>()), "Spanvectors are zero length");
4088 k = Math::pi<DataType>() / Tiny::calculate_opening_angle(v_1,v_2);
4089 offset = Tiny::calculate_opening_angle(Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2>{DataType(1.0), DataType(0.)}, v_1);
4090 }
4091
4092 template<typename Traits_>
4093 class Evaluator :
4094 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
4095 {
4096 public:
4097 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
4098 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
4099 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
4100 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
4101 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
4102
4103
4104 Tiny::Vector<DataType, 2> base_point;
4105 const DataType alpha, k, offset;
4106 const DataType eps;
4107
4108 explicit Evaluator(const CornerSingularity2D& func) :
4109 base_point(func.base_point),
4110 alpha(func.alpha),
4111 k(func.k),
4112 offset(func.offset),
4113 eps(Math::eps<DataType>())
4114 {
4115 }
4116
4117 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
4118 {
4119 //first calculate radius
4120 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4121 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4122 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4123 //TODO: Set x_rel to zero if r is very small?? <- Better conditioning?
4124 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4125 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4126 phi = (y >= DataType(0)) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4127 return alpha * Math::pow(r, k) * Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4128 }
4129
4130 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
4131 {
4132 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4133 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4134 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4135 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4136 const DataType y_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? y/r : DataType(0);
4137 //Note: While in practice we use a rotated coordinate system to express our polar-coordinate
4138 //based function, we have to use the "real" cos(phi) and sin(phi) values
4139 //for our base transformation, which are conveniently x_rel and y_rel
4140 //TODO: This could be badly conditioned for r -> 0, have to test this...
4141 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4142 phi = (y >= DataType(0)) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4143 const DataType ex = k * Math::pow(r, k-DataType(1));
4144 const DataType sval = Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4145 const DataType cval = Math::cos(k * (phi - offset));
4146 GradientType grad;
4147 grad[0] = alpha * ex * (x_rel * sval - y_rel * cval);
4148 grad[1] = alpha * ex * (y_rel * sval + x_rel * cval);
4149 return grad;
4150 }
4151
4152 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
4153 {
4154 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4155 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4156 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4157 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4158 const DataType y_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? y/r : DataType(0);
4159 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4160 phi = (y >= DataType(0)) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4161 const DataType ex = k * (k - DataType(1)) * Math::pow(r, k-DataType(2));
4162 const DataType sval = Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4163 const DataType cval = Math::cos(k * (phi - offset));
4164 HessianType hess;
4165 hess[0][0] = alpha * ex * ((Math::sqr(x_rel) - Math::sqr(y_rel)) * sval - DataType(2) * x_rel * y_rel * cval);
4166 hess[1][1] = -hess[0][0];

4513 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
4514 class HarmonicShellFunction :
4515 public Analytic::Function
4516 {
4517 public:
4518 static_assert((1 <= dim_) && (dim_ <= 3), "harmonic shell function is only implemented in 1D, 2D and 3D");
4519
4520 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
4521 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
4522 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
4523 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
4524 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
4525
4526 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
4527
4529 template<typename EvalTraits_>
4530 class Evaluator :
4531 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
4532 {
4533 public:
4535 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
4537 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
4539 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
4541 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
4543 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
4544
4545 private:
4547 const PointType _origin;
4548 const DataType _eps;
4549 const DataType _ln2; // = ln(2)
4550 const DataType _i2ln2; // = 1 /(2*ln(2))
4551
4552 public:
4554 explicit Evaluator(const HarmonicShellFunction& function) :
4555 _origin(function._origin),
4556 _eps(Math::eps<DataType>()),
4557 _ln2(Math::log(DataType(2))),
4558 _i2ln2(DataType(0.5)/_ln2)
4559 {
4560 }
4561
4562 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
4563 {
4564 if constexpr (dim_ == 1)
4565 return DataType(3) - DataType(2) * Math::abs(point[0] - _origin[0]);
4566 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4567 return DataType(1) - _i2ln2 * Math::log((point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr());
4568 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4569 return DataType(1) / (point - _origin).norm_euclid();
4570 else
4571 return DataType(0);
4572 }
4573
4574 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
4575 {
4576 const DataType norm_sqr = (point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr();
4577 if(norm_sqr < _eps)
4578 return GradientType::null();
4579
4580 GradientType grad(DataType(0));
4581 if constexpr (dim_ == 1)
4582 grad[0] = DataType(-2) * Math::signum(point[0] - _origin[0]);
4583 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4584 grad = (DataType(-1) / (_ln2 * norm_sqr)) * (point - _origin);
4585 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4586 grad = (DataType(1) / Math::pow(norm_sqr, DataType(1.5))) * (_origin - point);
4587
4588 return grad;
4589 }
4590
4591 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
4592 {
4593 const DataType norm_sqr = (point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr();
4594 if(norm_sqr < _eps)
4595 return HessianType::null();
4596
4597 HessianType hess(DataType(0));
4598 if constexpr(dim_ == 1)
4599 {
4600 // 1D hessian is null
4601 }
4602 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4603 {
4604 const DataType denom = DataType(1) / (_ln2 * Math::sqr(norm_sqr));
4605 hess[0][0] = denom * (Math::sqr(point[0] - _origin[0]) - Math::sqr(point[1] - _origin[1]));
4606 hess[1][1] = denom * (Math::sqr(point[1] - _origin[1]) - Math::sqr(point[0] - _origin[0]));
4607 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = denom * DataType(2) * (point[0] - _origin[0]) * (point[1] - _origin[1]);
4608 }
4609 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4610 {
4611 const DataType denom = DataType(1) / Math::pow(norm_sqr, DataType(2.5));
4612 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
4613 {
4614 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
4615 {
4616 if(i == j)
4617 {
4618 for(int k(0); k < dim_; ++k)
4619 hess[i][j] += DataType(k == i ? 2 : -1) * Math::sqr(point[k] - _origin[k]) * denom;
4620 }
4621 else
4622 {
4623 hess[i][j] = DataType(3) * (point[i] - _origin[i]) * (point[j] - _origin[j]) * denom;
4624 }
4625 }
4626 }
4627 }
4628 return hess;
4629 }
4630 }; // class HarmonicShellFunction::Evaluator<...>

4641 }

4645 _origin(origin)
